<div id="PJA12d013" class="doc letter">

<h2>From C.W.F. Dumas</h2>

<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">Lahaie 13e. Oct. 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Cest avec une trs-grande satisfaction que jai appris de Mr. Thaxter votre heureux rtablissement<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d014n1" id="PJA12d014n1-ptr">1</a>. Jespere que vous avez recouvr toutes vos forces, et quil ne vous reste aucun ressentiment de la violente fievre qui vous avoit attaqu. Pour se bien porter dans ce pays, il ne faut pas y mener une vie trop sdentaire, mais se donner du mouvement, et changer dair. Jaurois dj eu lhonneur de vous faire une visite et tenir compagnie. Mais labsence de ma femme, et fille, qui sont encore en Gueldre, et les choses interessantes qui se passent ici, et dont je ne voudrois pas interrompre le fil historique, mont retenu. Jespere de pouvoir le faire dans quelques semaines dici. Votre absence et maladie ont t causes que je nai pu vous communiquer la suite de mes dpches pour le Congrs. Je vous montrerai <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">coram</span> ce que vous nen avez pas vu. En attendant, je recommence par la prsente que vous voudrez bien, Monsieur, fermer aprs lavoir lue, et lui donner cours avec vos paquets<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d014n2" id="PJA12d014n2-ptr">2</a>. Jajouterai ici que je viens de recevoir une Lettre trs honnte et polie de la Socit <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Amore patriae</span>, qui est tablie  Rm, et qui moffre dtre un de leurs Membres, ou du Moins leur Correspondant. Je coupe court, pour ne pas trop vous fatiguer la premiere fois que jai lavantage de vous rpter, combien je suis pour tou-<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="ADMS-06-12-02-pb-0014">[14]</span>jours avec un vrai respect, Monsieur Votre trs-humble &amp; trs-obeissant serviteu</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="PJA12d014" class="trans letter">

 <h2>C. W. F. Dumas to John Adams: A Translation</h2>
 
<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		  <td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		  <td class="salutationRight">The Hague, 13 October 1781</td>
		</tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>It is with great satisfaction that I have learned from Mr. Thaxter of your recovery.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d014n1" id="PJA12d014n1-ptr">1</a> I hope you have regained all of your strength and that there is no trace left of your violent fever. To maintain good health in this country, one must not lead a sedentary life, but rather should keep moving and take in fresh air. I would have already had the honor to pay you a visit, but the absence of my wife and daughter, who are still in Gelderland, and my desire to not have any interruption in the interesting things going on here, have detained me. I hope to do it in a few weeks from now. Because of your absence and sickness, I did not send you the rest of my dispatches to Congress. I will show them to you in person. Meantime, let me start fresh with the enclosed one that, after having read it, sir, you would be so kind as to forward in your packets.<a class="ptr" href="#PJA12d014n2" id="PJA12d014n2-ptr">2</a> I will add here that I have just received a very honest and courteous letter from the <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Amore Patri</span> Society, established in Rotterdam, offering me membership, or at least a corresponding membership. I will cut this short, in order that I do not tire you the first time I have the privilege to repeat to you how I remain with true respect, sir, your very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Dumas</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#" id="PJA12d014sn1"></a>
<span class="docSource"><span class="dType"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr></span> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>). </span>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d014n1-ptr" id="PJA12d014n1">1</a>
<p>John Thaxter to Dumas, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-11-02-0362" class="document">24 Sept.</a> (vol. 11:492).</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA12d014n2-ptr" id="PJA12d014n2">2</a>
<p>Dumas probably enclosed his letter of 11 Oct. to the president of Congress (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Francis Wharton, ed., &lt;i&gt;The Revolutionary Diplomatic Correspondence of the United States&lt;/i&gt;, Washington, 1889; 6 vols. ]">Wharton, ed., <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Dipl. Corr. Amer. Rev.</span></span>, 4:771772).</p>
</div>
